assemblage.p:
If you wish to receive n payments per year for t years from a fund that earns interest rate r compounded n times per year, the present valuepresent value, PV, of the annuity must be
PV =\frac{P\left[1-\left(1+\dfrac{r}{n}\right)^{-nt}\right]}{\dfrac{r}{n}}
where each payment is P dollars.
